Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium for the ternary mixtures 2-methyl-1-propanol + n-hexane + 1-chlorobutane and 2-methyl-2-propanol + n-hexane + 1-chlorobutane and for the binary mixtures 2-methyl-1-propanol + n-hexane and 2-methyl-2-propanol + n-hexane have been studied at T = 298.15 K. The experimental data were checked for thermodynamic consistency using the method of van Ness. The isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium data of the ternary mixtures together with the corresponding constituent binary mixtures were correlated with the Wilson equation. The GE values obtained have been compared with those of the ternary mixtures 1-butanol or 2- butanol + n-hexane + 1-chlorobutane previously investigated.
Citation.sTitle: Isothermal Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium of Ternary Mixtures Containing 2-Methyl-1-propanol or 2-Methyl-2-propanol, n-Hexane, and 1-Chlorobutane at 298.15 K
